article.headline: Albany, N.Y. 23, Fordham 20
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- Jason Fralicker kicked a 20-yard field goal, hit third of the game, early in the fourth quarter and Albany, N.Y., went on to beat Fordham 23-20 Saturday night. Frolicker's 35-yard field goal at 7:52 of the first quarter opened the game's scoring and the Great Danes (1-1) never trailed. Albany's Vinny Esposito fired a 10-yard TD pass to Marcus Miles with 59 seconds remaining to increase the lead to 10-0. John Skelton of the Rams connected on a 48-yard pass to Jason Caldwell at 14:00 of the second quarter to cut the deficit to 10-7. Frolicker then kicked a 37-yarder to make it 13-7 with 28 seconds to play in the half, but Skelton's 15-yard pass to David Moore 26 seconds later got Fordham (1-1) even at 13. Dan Beigel's 1-yard run at 7:51 of the third quarter put the visitors on top 20-13. Jonte Coven's 6-yard run at 5:21 enabled Fordham to gain a 20-20 tie. Dave McCarty ran 26 times for 143 yards for Albany, and Esposito connected on 17 of 26 passes for 173 yards.
